</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BBB36E0FFF3FF83B7F80D30FEA435A9" blockId="3.[174,1232,1042,1229]" pageId="3" pageNumber="12">
Diagnosis. The female is characterized by the hind coxa black, trochanter red; fore tarsal claws enlarged basally (into lobes) and emarginated apically (
<figureCitation id="133F2A65FFF3FF83B4C40D10FB9B3529" box="[991,1055,1074,1101]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1687,1709]" captionTargetBox="[174,1225,907,1659]" captionTargetId="figure-355@2.[174,1225,907,1659]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 2. Exeristes spp., female. 1 — E. roborator, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 2 — E. longiseta, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 3 — E. arundinis, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 4 — E. denticulator, holotype, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 5 — E. ruficollis, lectotype, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 6 — E. arundinis, fore tarsal claw (lateral view); 7 — E. ruficollis, lectotype, hind femur and tibia (lateral view); 8 — E. denticulator, holotype, hind tibia and tarsus (lateral view); 9 — E. denticulator, holotype, propodeum and tergites I–II of metasoma (dorsal view); 10 — E. roborator, propodeum and tergites I–II of metasoma (dorsal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404124/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="12">fig. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="B970EAF2FFF3FF83B3360D10FBBF3528" box="[1069,1083,1074,1100]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="12">6</emphasis>
); ovipositor tip subapically tuberculated (
<figureCitation id="133F2A65FFF3FF83B50D0D70FDDD3509" box="[534,601,1106,1133]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1687,1709]" captionTargetBox="[174,1225,907,1659]" captionTargetId="figure-355@2.[174,1225,907,1659]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 2. Exeristes spp., female. 1 — E. roborator, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 2 — E. longiseta, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 3 — E. arundinis, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 4 — E. denticulator, holotype, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 5 — E. ruficollis, lectotype, ovipositor tip (lateral view); 6 — E. arundinis, fore tarsal claw (lateral view); 7 — E. ruficollis, lectotype, hind femur and tibia (lateral view); 8 — E. denticulator, holotype, hind tibia and tarsus (lateral view); 9 — E. denticulator, holotype, propodeum and tergites I–II of metasoma (dorsal view); 10 — E. roborator, propodeum and tergites I–II of metasoma (dorsal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404124/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="12">fig. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133F2A65FFF3FF83B5720D70FDF33508" box="[617,631,1106,1132]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,912,934]" captionTargetBox="[174,1232,174,882]" captionTargetId="figure-392@3.[174,1232,174,882]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. Exeristes spp., male. 1 — E. arundinis, habitus (lateral view); 2 — E. longiseta, habitus (lateral view); 3 — E. ruficollis, head and mesosoma (lateral view); 4 — E. roborator, clypeus (frontal view); 5 — E. arundinis, hind tarsus (lateral view); 6 — E. roborator, hind tarsus (lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404126" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404126/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis id="B970EAF2FFF3FF83B5720D70FDF33508" box="[617,631,1106,1132]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="12">3</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
); metasomal tergites elongated; and hind tarsus with fifth tarsomere about 1.2 times longer than second tarsomere (
<figureCitation id="133F2A65FFF3FF83B4F10D50FBAE35E9" box="[1002,1066,1138,1165]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,912,934]" captionTargetBox="[174,1232,174,882]" captionTargetId="figure-392@3.[174,1232,174,882]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. Exeristes spp., male. 1 — E. arundinis, habitus (lateral view); 2 — E. longiseta, habitus (lateral view); 3 — E. ruficollis, head and mesosoma (lateral view); 4 — E. roborator, clypeus (frontal view); 5 — E. arundinis, hind tarsus (lateral view); 6 — E. roborator, hind tarsus (lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404126" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404126/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="12">fig. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="B970EAF2FFF3FF83B3230D51FBC235E9" box="[1080,1094,1139,1165]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="12">5</emphasis>
). The male generally resembles female and has black scape, pedicel, and all coxae; red all trochanters (
<figureCitation id="133F2A65FFF3FF83B7AD0D90FF7035A9" box="[182,244,1202,1229]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,912,934]" captionTargetBox="[174,1232,174,882]" captionTargetId="figure-392@3.[174,1232,174,882]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. Exeristes spp., male. 1 — E. arundinis, habitus (lateral view); 2 — E. longiseta, habitus (lateral view); 3 — E. ruficollis, head and mesosoma (lateral view); 4 — E. roborator, clypeus (frontal view); 5 — E. arundinis, hind tarsus (lateral view); 6 — E. roborator, hind tarsus (lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404126" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404126/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="12">fig. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133F2A65FFF3FF83B61A0D90FE8B35A8" box="[257,271,1202,1228]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[170,203,1808,1830]" captionTargetBox="[257,1165,1011,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-418@1.[257,1165,1011,1773]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1. The Carpathian Exeristes spp. distribution map. Yellow circle — E. roborator; red circle — E. longiseta; green circle — E. arundinis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404122" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404122/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis id="B970EAF2FFF3FF83B61A0D90FE8B35A8" box="[257,271,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="12">1</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBB36E0FFF3FF83B7F80DD0FCC23469" blockId="3.[227,838,1266,1293]" box="[227,838,1266,1293]" pageId="3" pageNumber="12">
